const articleData = {
  title: "Top 10 SEO Trends Shaping the Philippines Market in 2024",
  excerpt: "Discover the latest SEO trends specifically impacting Philippine businesses, from local search optimization to AI-powered content strategies that are driving results.",
  author: {
    name: "Miguel Rodriguez",
    bio: "Miguel is a Senior SEO Strategist at Bright Forge SEO with over 8 years of experience in Philippine digital marketing. He specializes in local SEO and has helped 200+ Filipino businesses achieve top rankings.",
    avatar: "/images/team/miguel-rodriguez.jpg",
    linkedin: "https://linkedin.com/in/miguel-rodriguez-seo"
  },
  publishDate: "2024-03-15",
  readTime: "8 min",
  category: "SEO Strategy",
  tags: ["SEO Trends", "Philippines SEO", "Local Search", "AI SEO", "Mobile Optimization", "Voice Search"],
  featuredImage: "/images/blog/seo-trends-philippines-2024.jpg",
  content: `
    <p>The SEO landscape in the Philippines is evolving rapidly, driven by changing consumer behaviors, technological advances, and Google's continuous algorithm updates. As we navigate 2024, Filipino businesses need to stay ahead of these trends to maintain competitive advantage.</p>
    
    <h2 id="mobile-first-dominance">1. Mobile-First Indexing is Non-Negotiable</h2>
    <p>With over 76 million mobile internet users in the Philippines, mobile optimization is no longer optional. Google's mobile-first indexing means your mobile site version is what Google primarily uses for ranking.</p>
    
    <blockquote>
      "Our data shows that 85% of Philippine web traffic comes from mobile devices, making mobile optimization the foundation of any successful SEO strategy." - Google Philippines
    </blockquote>
    
    <h3>Key Mobile Optimization Strategies:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Implement responsive design with fast loading times</li>
      <li>Optimize images and use next-gen formats like WebP</li>
      <li>Ensure touch-friendly navigation and buttons</li>
      <li>Use structured data for rich snippets on mobile</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2 id="local-seo-filipino-context">2. Hyper-Local SEO with Filipino Context</h2>
    <p>Local search is becoming increasingly sophisticated. Filipino consumers are searching for businesses "near me" in Tagalog, Cebuano, and other local languages.</p>
    
    <h3>Essential Local SEO Tactics for 2024:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Optimize Google My Business with Filipino language content</li>
      <li>Include local landmarks and barangay references</li>
      <li>Build citations on Filipino directories and platforms</li>
      <li>Encourage reviews in local languages</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2 id="ai-content-optimization">3. AI-Powered Content Optimization</h2>
    <p>Artificial Intelligence is revolutionizing how we create and optimize content. However, the human touch remains crucial for understanding Filipino culture and context.</p>
    
    <h2 id="voice-search-tagalog">4. Voice Search in Tagalog and Regional Languages</h2>
    <p>Voice search adoption is growing rapidly in the Philippines, with many users preferring to search in their native language.</p>
    
    <h2 id="video-seo-tiktok">5. Video SEO Beyond YouTube</h2>
    <p>TikTok and Facebook video content are becoming major search traffic drivers in the Philippines.</p>
    
    <h2 id="e-commerce-seo">6. E-commerce SEO for Local Marketplaces</h2>
    <p>With the rise of Shopee, Lazada, and local e-commerce platforms, optimizing for marketplace visibility is crucial.</p>
    
    <h2 id="core-web-vitals">7. Core Web Vitals as Ranking Factors</h2>
    <p>Page experience signals continue to gain importance, especially for Philippine businesses competing globally.</p>
    
    <h2 id="featured-snippets">8. Featured Snippets Optimization</h2>
    <p>Capturing featured snippets for Filipino search queries can dramatically increase visibility and traffic.</p>
    
    <h2 id="semantic-search">9. Semantic Search and Entity Optimization</h2>
    <p>Google's understanding of context and intent is improving, requiring more sophisticated content strategies.</p>
    
    <h2 id="sustainability-seo">10. Sustainability and Social Impact SEO</h2>
    <p>Filipino consumers increasingly value businesses that demonstrate environmental and social responsibility.</p>
    
    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>Success in Philippine SEO requires understanding both global trends and local nuances. Businesses that adapt these strategies while maintaining authentic Filipino connections will dominate search results in 2024.</p>
    
    <p>Ready to implement these trends for your business? Contact our team for a customized SEO strategy that speaks to your Filipino audience.</p>
  `,
